# How to install CBL
Step 1: Go to the releases tab and download the source files, you will get the cbl all its supporting libraries.
Step 2: Copy the libraries of code in the directory where your project will be saved.
Step 3: Go make a new project and write:
        from cbl import *
       
Step 4: Go write the CBL Code!

Note: You can also use other libraries like cbl math if you want
Make sure you download official versions of CBL, betas are not highly suggested.


NOTE: Older versions of CBL like CBL 1.0 or beta versions will be deleted from the versions tab if a new version has been released, because we consider those versions as "not supported". CBL can work in Mac, Windows and Linux, as long as you have Python.
